###
### jEdit hints
### By Slava Pestov <sp@gjt.org>
###

tip.0=These tips can be disabled in the File->Global Options dialog
tip.1=Press C+d C+d to delete the current line
tip.2=Press C+d C+s to delete from the start of the current line to the caret
tip.3=Press C+d C+f to delete from the caret to the end of the current line
tip.4=Try File->Open URL to fetch files via ftp & http
tip.5=The last 25 pasted strings are listed in the Edit->Paste Previous dialog
tip.6=The Buffers menu displays (modified) next to files that have changed
tip.7=Try File->Send to send the current file via e-mail
tip.8=jEdit performs syntax colorizing when printing, too
tip.9=A+UP and A+DOWN can be used instead of PageUp and PageDown
tip.10=Try disabling Syntax Colorizing to speed jEdit up a bit
tip.11=The -nosplash command line switch makes jEdit start a little faster
tip.12=When editing TeX files, File->Compile invokes amstex/latex for you
tip.13=The Escape key does the equivalent of pushing Cancel in a dialog
tip.14=The Enter key does the equivalent of pushing OK in a dialog
tip.15=Tab and Shift+Tab shift to the next and previous element in a dialog
tip.16=Give the Search->HyperSearch command a go sometime
tip.17=Press C+t to save the current position, and C+y to go back to it later
tip.18=C+LEFT and C+RIGHT move to the previous and next word, respectively
tip.19=C+UP and C+DOWN move to the next or previous paragraph
tip.20=Pressing Shift with an arrow key extends the selection in that direction
tip.21=A+LEFT and A+RIGHT shift a block of text left or right by one Tab
tip.22=Use markers to move around large documents
tip.23=The Open URL command isn't just for URLs: file names can be entered too
tip.24=The Save To URL command isn't just for URLs: file names can be entered too
tip.25=Try Edit->Format Text to make text look "nicer"
tip.26=C+x, C+c and C+v work in all text fields, not just the main editor
tip.27=jEdit home page: <http://www.gjt.org/~sp/jedit.html>
tip.28=Somelongword... Som<C+b> -> Somelongword... Try C+b sometime
tip.29=If the caret is after a bracket, C+] will go to the matching one
tip.30=C+[ selects the current code block ( { ... } )
tip.31=Press F10 and use the arrow keys for mouse-free menu operation
tip.32=Undo and Redo remember the last 100 editing actions
tip.33=Try Edit->Tabs to Spaces if you do not like using Tabs
tip.34=Try Edit->Spaces to Tabs if someone sent you a file with soft tabs
tip.35=jEdit can transparently edit GZipped files
tip.36=Power users: edit jedit_gui.props to change the menu bar
tip.37=You can change menu item shortcuts in File->Global Options->Shortcuts
tip.38=jEdit is Open Source: give copies to your friends
tip.39=jEdit is Open Source: you can edit the source code to suit your needs
tip.40=Files can be opened read only for browsing with the -readonly switch
tip.41=When started with no parameters, jEdit opens files from the last session
tip.42=Menus and menu items can be selected with A+<underlined char>
tip.43=Markers are saved across editing sessions to .<filename>.marks
tip.44=If jEdit crashes, look in #<filename># for autosaved data
tip.45=When saving, jEdit first backs the file up to <filename>~
tip.46=Use File->New View to create a new editor window
tip.47=Auto indent coolness: press Tab on an indented line to insert a real Tab
tip.48=When editing HTML files, use File->Open Selection to check links
tip.49=To select lots of text, press C+t at the start and C+u at the end
tip.50=You can have more than one view editing a buffer (File->New View)
tip.51=Press F1 for help
tip.52=The window size is saved between editing sessions
tip.53=File->Open Recent contains up to 8 previously opened file names
tip.54=jEdit can be customized to your needs in the File->Global Options dialog
tip.55=Mac users: jEdit uses Mac-style shortcuts: C+z, C+x, C+c, C+v, etc
tip.56=Windows users: try selecting the Windows L&F in the Options dialog
tip.57=CDE/Motif users: try selecting the Motif L&F in the Options dialog
tip.58=Mac users: try selecting the MacOS L&F in the Options dialog
tip.59=To GZip the current file, do a Save As to <filename>.gz
tip.60=HTML mode colorizes JavaScripts in <script> tags - try it!
tip.61=If jEdit crashes during an autosave, you can still recover your file
tip.62=Press C+e C+j to center the current line on the screen
tip.63=Double click on a bracket to select the code block it delimits
tip.64=C+t saves the current position, C+e C+x flips between it and the caret
tip.65=Emacs users: the anchor works like the Emacs "mark"
tip.66=C+i will go to the first non-whitespace character of the current line
tip.67=If you prefer soft tabs, specify so in the Options dialog
tip.68=Try out the commenting commands in Edit->Code Block Operations
tip.69=Regexp coolness: $1-$9 inserts the contents of subexpression 1-9
tip.70=Use UP/DOWN to recall the last 25 search & replace strings
tip.71=Use Edit->Paste Predefined to insert frequently used strings
tip.72=Jikes users: try `jikes +E' for jEdit to parse the errors
tip.73=Try File->Save All Buffers to save all open files
tip.74=A block caret can be enabled in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.75=Use File->Reload to reload the current file from disk
tip.76=Try right clicking on the text area
tip.77=There is a `Keep Dialog' option in Search & Replace
tip.78=The tool bar can be disabled in File->Global Options->General
tip.79=Quoted literals that don't end on the same line are shown differently
tip.80=HTML entities that don't end on the same line are shown differently
tip.81=The tab size can be set on a buffer-specific basis in File->Buffer Options
tip.82=F11 and F12 open the previous and next buffer, respectively
tip.83=The File->Buffer Options dialog sets properties on a per-buffer basis
tip.84=If you prefer Indent on Enter, enable it in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.85=It is possible to send the selection only in File->Send
tip.86=The help viewer can be used as a simple WWW browser
tip.87=For information about installed plugins, see Help->Plugin Help Contents
tip.88=You can change the default edit mode in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.81=Check out the jEdit plugin page <http://www.icg-online.de/jedit/>
tip.82=Pressing Insert toggles overwrite mode
tip.83=Check out Help->Help Contents->Advanced Text Editing->History Text Fields
tip.84=jEdit supports both literal and regular expression search & replace
tip.85=jEdit supports multi file search and replace
tip.86=Change plugin settings in File->Plugin Options
tip.87=EOL markers can be disabled in File->Global Options->Editor
tip.88=To go to the first and last visible character, press HOME HOME and END END
tip.89=To go to the first and last character of the file, press HOME and END 3 times
